   "info" : "<table width=\"100%\" summary=\"page for JohnsonJohnson\"><tr><td>JohnsonJohnson</td><td style=\"text-align: right;\">R Documentation</td></tr></table>\\n<h2>Quarterly Earnings per Johnson &amp; Johnson Share</h2>\\n<h3>Description</h3>\\n<p>Quarterly earnings (dollars) per Johnson &amp; Johnson share 1960&ndash;80.\\n</p>\\n<h3>Usage</h3>\\n<pre>JohnsonJohnson</pre>\\n<h3>Format</h3>\\n<p>A quarterly time series\\n</p>\\n<h3>Source</h3>\\n<p>Shumway, R. H. and Stoffer, D. S. (2000)\\n<em>Time Series Analysis and its Applications</em>.\\nSecond Edition.  Springer.  Example 1.1.\\n</p>\\n<h3>Examples</h3>\\n<pre>\\nrequire(stats); require(graphics)\\nJJ &lt;- log10(JohnsonJohnson)\\nplot(JJ)\\n## This example gives a possible-non-convergence warning on some\\n## platforms, but does seem to converge on x86 Linux and Windows.\\n(fit &lt;- StructTS(JJ, type = \"BSM\"))\\ntsdiag(fit)\\nsm &lt;- tsSmooth(fit)\\nplot(cbind(JJ, sm[, 1], sm[, 3]-0.5), plot.type = \"single\",\\n     col = c(\"black\", \"green\", \"blue\"))\\nabline(h = -0.5, col = \"grey60\")\\nmonthplot(fit)\\n</pre>\\n",
